= Internal Factions of the RGA

{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The Communists, the left of the party, advocate radical change and revolution to achieve a communist society.">Communist</span>!} strength: [+ communist_strength : strength +], dissent: [+ communist_dissent : dissent +]

{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The Marxists are not as radical as the communists, but they too see socialism through a Marxist lense. They are represented by the Workers' Caucus.">Marxist</span>!} strength: [+ marxist_strength : strength +], dissent: [+ marxist_dissent : dissent +]

{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The Anarchists and Libertarians seek to achieve a stateless society in the DoR. Uniquely, they support participation in elections.">Anarchist</span>!} strength: [+ anarchist_strength : strength +], dissent: [+ anarchist_dissent : dissent +]

{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The Pan Socialists are the glue of the party. They seek unity within the RGA, as well as cooperation with other left-wing parties.">Pan Socialist</span>!} strength: [+ pansocialist_strength : strength +], dissent: [+ pansocialist_dissent : dissent +]

{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The Reformists seek to achieve socialism by electoralism and reform, rejecting more radical methods. They are represented by the Rose Caucus.">Reformist</span>!} strength: [+ reformist_strength : strength +], dissent: [+ reformist_dissent : dissent +]

{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The Liberal Socialists and Classical Radicals of the party believe in a syncretism of liberal and socialist values. They support the extension of democracy and social reforms.">Liberal</span>!} strength: [+ radlib_strength : strength +], dissent: [+ radlib_dissent : dissent +]

